1
00:00:03,280 --> 00:00:05,400
R, Sh, T. I'm done.

2
00:00:05,520 --> 00:00:07,880
Very nice, good job, sweetie.

3
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:08,880
Good job, babe,

4
00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:11,800
Now let’s see you say it all from the beginning,

5
00:00:12,200 --> 00:00:14,880
But quietly, in your heart, in your inner voice.

6
00:00:15,040 --> 00:00:16,880
Okay. A... go on.

7
00:00:16,960 --> 00:00:20,080
So, in short, I talked to my mom. Well, that’s not a good start.

8
00:00:20,400 --> 00:00:21,240
Funny.

9
00:00:21,320 --> 00:00:22,520
It’s about Rosh Hashanah.

10
00:00:22,760 --> 00:00:24,040
What, Rosh Hashanah is still a few months away, right?

11
00:00:24,120 --> 00:00:25,560
No, it’s in a month and a bit.

12
00:00:26,120 --> 00:00:27,640
Anyway, my mom wants us to celebrate the holiday at her place

13
00:00:27,760 --> 00:00:29,680
!She’s inviting the parents too

14
00:00:31,240 --> 00:00:32,720
But we were at their place last year, right?

15
00:00:32,800 --> 00:00:36,400
No, we were at our parents' for Passover at your parents'.

16
00:00:36,960 --> 00:00:38,920
Can’t we skip it? You think?

17
00:00:39,640 --> 00:00:41,400
Alright, babe. Okay, I’m done.

18
00:00:41,480 --> 00:00:42,520
'Yep', babe.

19
00:00:44,120 --> 00:00:45,080
Sweetheart.

20
00:00:48,280 --> 00:00:50,880
Look at me, look at me and...

21
00:01:01,600 --> 00:01:05,880
Hey there. Well, hey, great, I was really worried.

22
00:01:06,920 --> 00:01:07,920
How’s it going, Riki?

23
00:01:09,200 --> 00:01:11,720
Girls, don’t run, don’t touch the walls,

24
00:01:11,880 --> 00:01:14,360
I spent all yesterday on my hands and knees scrubbing.

25
00:01:16,520 --> 00:01:18,640
Pinchas, Shabbat Shalom. Well, Shabbat Shalom, sit down.

26
00:01:18,720 --> 00:01:19,720
How are you?

27
00:01:19,800 --> 00:01:20,720
Riki, are you listening?

28
00:01:20,840 --> 00:01:22,360
I just talked to my mom on the way here,

29
00:01:22,440 --> 00:01:24,600
!She’s inviting you to celebrate the holiday with them.

30
00:01:24,680 --> 00:01:25,520
How nice.

31
00:01:25,600 --> 00:01:26,560
Really? Well, yes.

32
00:01:26,640 --> 00:01:27,880
She didn’t have to.

33
00:01:27,960 --> 00:01:30,000
How nice, really sweet of her.

34
00:01:30,080 --> 00:01:33,000
We’d love to come, sit down, it’s been a while since we were there.

35
00:01:33,480 --> 00:01:35,880
Yeah, but until Rosh Hashanah, who knows.

36
00:01:35,960 --> 00:01:37,080
What do you mean?

37
00:01:37,160 --> 00:01:39,320
Why does your mom need this?

38
00:01:39,440 --> 00:01:40,720
To cook for all of us?

39
00:01:40,880 --> 00:01:43,280
Don’t forget she’s not a little girl anymore, your mom.

40
00:01:43,360 --> 00:01:44,920
Nonsense, Riki, she loves it.

41
00:01:45,760 --> 00:01:48,760
Do I need to bring something? Sweet stuff for Rosh Hashanah?

42
00:01:49,320 --> 00:01:51,800
I have a calendar in the kitchen, I’ll go check.

43
00:01:52,360 --> 00:01:53,640
What, Riki, it’s really just a month and a bit away.

44
00:01:53,720 --> 00:01:54,840
What’s up with her? Why is she like that?

45
00:01:54,920 --> 00:01:58,160
Because on the other hand, maybe she’s right, why does your mom need to cook for all of us?

46
00:01:58,240 --> 00:02:01,880
Oh, I’m dying, I love your mom’s food.

47
00:02:02,240 --> 00:02:05,440
Especially those little stuffed circles. Yum, mikhalehta.

48
00:02:05,920 --> 00:02:08,039
Yeah, maybe not, no, no, no,

49
00:02:08,160 --> 00:02:10,440
Was it a Gimel or a Zayin?

50
00:02:10,720 --> 00:02:14,760
Oh, and I’m just remembering her spicy fish, it’s to die for.

51
00:02:14,880 --> 00:02:16,240
Shai, talk to your mom, I need an answer

52
00:02:16,320 --> 00:02:17,840
because I want to let my mom know. Well, okay.

53
00:02:18,240 --> 00:02:20,720
She has this really spicy dough, spicy.

54
00:02:20,800 --> 00:02:22,840
Just thinking about it makes me sweat.

55
00:02:23,200 --> 00:02:24,080
Will there be kubbeh too?

56
00:02:24,920 --> 00:02:27,320
No, kubbeh is from a different cuisine.

57
00:02:31,800 --> 00:02:33,040
Well, Mom, what do you say?

58
00:02:33,640 --> 00:02:37,040
I don’t know, Shayka, why do we need all this mess?

59
00:02:37,200 --> 00:02:38,880
I agree with you, it really is a big mess.

60
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:42,920
It’s really nice of them, but I have a home and I’m good here.

61
00:02:43,200 --> 00:02:45,640
Why do I have to go to strangers' houses?

62
00:02:45,720 --> 00:02:48,920
Mom, Mom, they’re not strangers. Well, I know.

63
00:02:49,480 --> 00:02:51,960
But I don’t feel like going. Well, neither do I.

64
00:02:52,040 --> 00:02:53,480
So what do we do? How do we get out of this?

65
00:02:53,600 --> 00:02:57,440
Because you know they'll be really offended, they’re really sensitive people.

66
00:02:57,560 --> 00:03:00,760
I know. Well, it’s really important to them, their honor.

67
00:03:00,840 --> 00:03:05,840
I don’t want to generalize, and I don’t want to sound, you know what.

68
00:03:05,920 --> 00:03:08,720
God forbid. Well, but they, specifically them,

69
00:03:08,800 --> 00:03:11,040
are really sensitive. Well, yeah.

70
00:03:12,720 --> 00:03:16,200
Wait, where is Itamar celebrating the holiday? Well, I don’t know.

71
00:03:17,520 --> 00:03:20,440
Right, I can’t celebrate the holiday without my kids.

72
00:03:20,520 --> 00:03:22,480
Of course, they’re your kids.

73
00:03:24,360 --> 00:03:27,160
Wait, what about Dad? Since the invitation, he’s been drooling on the living room carpet.

74
00:03:27,800 --> 00:03:28,840
You leave Dad to me.

75
00:03:32,320 --> 00:03:34,640
And what about the twin sister? Is she still in Los Angeles?

76
00:03:34,720 --> 00:03:35,680
Yeah, yeah—

77
00:03:35,760 --> 00:03:37,360
What do they do there? Falafel, right?

78
00:03:37,440 --> 00:03:39,960
No, no. High tech. Well, oh, I remembered something like that.

79
00:03:40,080 --> 00:03:41,760
And will they be at the holiday? Well, no, they’re not coming.

80
00:03:41,840 --> 00:03:44,600
Yeah, fine. The main thing is we’ll be there. Well, yeah.

81
00:03:45,280 --> 00:03:47,360
Hey there. Well, hi, Shabbat Shalom.

82
00:03:47,480 --> 00:03:49,400
What’s up? I need to use the bathroom.

83
00:03:49,480 --> 00:03:50,440
What’s this, are you alone?

84
00:03:50,520 --> 00:03:52,680
No, Michal is downstairs, she’s looking for parking.

85
00:03:52,800 --> 00:03:54,160
I just came up first because I had to use the bathroom.

86
00:03:54,240 --> 00:03:57,160
And the kids are okay? Well, yeah, of course they’re okay,

87
00:03:57,240 --> 00:03:58,440
they’re on their way, I have to...

88
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:01,200
What do you mean on their way? Are they walking by themselves? Well, where are they coming from?

89
00:04:01,320 --> 00:04:04,640
No, Smadar will pick them up later. Well, I’m running to the bathroom.

90
00:04:04,720 --> 00:04:07,280
They sat with Smadar? Well, yeah, of course they sat with Smadar.

91
00:04:07,360 --> 00:04:10,000
Dad, what’s wrong with you? If I don’t go to the bathroom now, it’ll end in tears.

92
00:04:10,080 --> 00:04:11,080
And mostly ours.

93
00:04:12,920 --> 00:04:15,080
What’s that? I thought I heard Tamar.

94
00:04:15,560 --> 00:04:17,640
That woman can hear a pin drop.

95
00:04:18,360 --> 00:04:20,320
Yeah, yeah, he’s here, he went to the bathroom, Riki.

96
00:04:20,800 --> 00:04:24,080
Great, I was really worried, you know he has a really small bladder.

97
00:04:24,160 --> 00:04:25,440
Now I know.

98
00:04:25,600 --> 00:04:27,640
What’s going on with the holiday? What’s the deal?

99
00:04:27,720 --> 00:04:30,200
I don’t know, there are a few problems.

100
00:04:30,280 --> 00:04:32,640
What problems? We’re at the parents’ for the holiday.

101
00:04:32,760 --> 00:04:35,960
Yeah, and where will your kids be? Well, Itamar and Adam?

102
00:04:36,040 --> 00:04:37,960
Do you have more that I don’t know about?

103
00:04:39,120 --> 00:04:44,000
So Pinchas, if you don’t have anything smart to say, well, it’s better you talk about the weather.

104
00:04:44,560 --> 00:04:46,880
No, Shai, it’s just that my mom doesn’t want to leave my siblings alone.

105
00:04:46,960 --> 00:04:49,720
We don’t want to burden your mom with the fact that we’re all coming.

106
00:04:49,800 --> 00:04:52,520
What face will I have leaving my kids alone for the holiday?

107
00:04:52,600 --> 00:04:55,200
Okay, but Riki, your kids might have plans.

108
00:04:55,280 --> 00:04:56,320
No way,

109
00:04:56,680 --> 00:04:59,880
my kids know that the first thing they need to do is tell Mom.

110
00:05:00,440 --> 00:05:01,480
Right, Pinchas?

111
00:05:01,960 --> 00:05:04,320
It’s hotter today than usual for this season.

112
00:05:06,760 --> 00:05:07,600
High humidity.

113
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:11,240
I wanted to stop on the way, well, but Michal didn’t let me.

114
00:05:11,320 --> 00:05:14,200
Okay, tell me, Itamar, well, where are you and your bladder for the holiday?

115
00:05:14,360 --> 00:05:16,720
What holiday? Well, what holiday? Rosh Hashanah.

116
00:05:16,800 --> 00:05:18,000
Where are you? Here, right?

117
00:05:18,080 --> 00:05:19,680
How should I know? That’s still a long time away.

118
00:05:19,800 --> 00:05:22,440
Apparently not for them. In their calendar, it’s already holiday eve.

119
00:05:22,520 --> 00:05:25,760
Don’t mess with my head. Well, I need to know, are you here for the holiday?

120
00:05:27,560 --> 00:05:30,880
No, I’m in the Maldives. Well, no way, Maldives.

121
00:05:31,360 --> 00:05:34,360
So now there’s really no problem, right? It’s just Adam left.

122
00:05:34,440 --> 00:05:37,240
My mom won’t have any problem hosting one more person.

123
00:05:37,320 --> 00:05:40,600
Shani, you can’t decide that for her, you need to check.

124
00:05:40,680 --> 00:05:42,600
Okay, I’ll go call her, I’ll find out.

125
00:05:47,600 --> 00:05:49,760
Are you out of your mind?

126
00:05:50,440 --> 00:05:51,760
Who celebrates a holiday abroad?

127
00:05:52,320 --> 00:05:55,080
And with strangers, with foreigners?

128
00:05:55,640 --> 00:05:56,960
Pinchas, say something to him.

129
00:05:57,440 --> 00:06:01,120
It was cool yesterday, today it’s hot and it’s only going to get hotter.

130
00:06:05,200 --> 00:06:06,880
Hello. Hey, Mom.

131
00:06:06,960 --> 00:06:08,880
Hey sweetie, what’s up? Are they coming?

132
00:06:08,960 --> 00:06:11,720
It’s not confirmed yet. I told you she’d cause trouble.

133
00:06:12,200 --> 00:06:14,600
No, no, no, she really wants to come, really,

134
00:06:14,680 --> 00:06:17,640
She just asked me to check if it’s okay for Adam, Shai’s brother, to come too

135
00:06:17,720 --> 00:06:18,920
because he’s alone for the holiday.

136
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:20,560
What do you mean, what’s the problem? What problem?

137
00:06:20,640 --> 00:06:21,720
Why are you even asking?

138
00:06:21,800 --> 00:06:23,920
I don’t know, but she asked me to check, she feels awkward.

139
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:25,640
{Yoo, she can bring whoever she wants whenever she wants.}

140
00:06:25,720 --> 00:06:27,800
It’s family, right?

141
00:06:27,880 --> 00:06:29,160
It’s fine, Mom, she’s not listening. Great.

142
00:06:29,240 --> 00:06:31,000
And don’t you dare bring anything, you hear? Nothing.

143
00:06:32,080 --> 00:06:34,880
Okay, Mom, I’ll talk to her when it’s settled.

144
00:06:34,960 --> 00:06:36,440
Alright, bye sweetie. Bye.

145
00:06:36,520 --> 00:06:37,960
What’s she saying? Of course it’s fine for her brother to come.

146
00:06:38,520 --> 00:06:40,720
And all these arrangements are starting to drive me crazy.

147
00:06:40,840 --> 00:06:42,600
You don’t have to, you know. You can separate forces too.

148
00:06:43,360 --> 00:06:45,320
Forget it, son, Shai, it’ll be fine.

149
00:06:45,400 --> 00:06:47,120
Who? What?

150
00:06:47,680 --> 00:06:48,760
Nothing.

151
00:06:48,840 --> 00:06:49,720
Nothing at all.

152
00:06:52,720 --> 00:06:55,200
Mom, what happened to Dad? Why did he swallow the doctor’s advice?

153
00:06:55,760 --> 00:06:58,440
Where are the kids? Did something happen? Nothing happened.

154
00:06:58,680 --> 00:07:01,120
Michal’s downstairs, looking for parking,

155
00:07:01,680 --> 00:07:03,320
the kids were with Smadar, and she’ll drop them off later, she’ll call from downstairs.

156
00:07:03,400 --> 00:07:06,640
How nice. Smadar, I just had coffee with her at the mall this week.

157
00:07:07,200 --> 00:07:10,880
What? We ran into each other.

158
00:07:10,960 --> 00:07:12,840
So we sat and chatted a bit.

159
00:07:12,920 --> 00:07:14,880
She’s doing well: in Hadar, does Orna know?

160
00:07:15,200 --> 00:07:16,880
Are you kidding me? She looks great in Hadar.

161
00:07:16,960 --> 00:07:19,760
When she arrives, tell her to come up a bit.

162
00:07:19,840 --> 00:07:21,600
What do you mean come up? What’s wrong with you? What’s there to...

163
00:07:21,680 --> 00:07:23,760
Guys, do you remember we’re divorced?

164
00:07:23,840 --> 00:07:25,720
Just because you divorced her doesn’t mean I did too.

165
00:07:25,800 --> 00:07:29,080
I never had a problem with Smadar.

166
00:07:29,560 --> 00:07:31,520
Mom, I don’t want to talk about Smadar anymore, got it?

167
00:07:31,640 --> 00:07:33,000
Michal needs to come in any minute, and I don’t want to talk about it anymore,

168
00:07:33,080 --> 00:07:34,840
enough already, we’re not talking about it anymore. Okay, okay. What did I even say?

169
00:07:34,920 --> 00:07:37,360
I don’t understand why you’re so sensitive about it.

170
00:07:37,800 --> 00:07:39,960
What, are you talking about Smadar? Enough already, come on.

171
00:07:40,160 --> 00:07:42,040
Okay, Michal looks good in Hadar too,

172
00:07:42,760 --> 00:07:45,440
but not like Smadar.

173
00:07:45,880 --> 00:07:47,360
And just because she wears clothes for a three-year-old

174
00:07:47,640 --> 00:07:50,240
doesn’t make her anything special. Mom, enough, stop.

175
00:07:50,640 --> 00:07:53,680
No, I’m dying, there’s no parking at all. You won’t believe where the house is.

176
00:07:53,760 --> 00:07:56,760
I just gave up and dumped the car, I’m dying.

177
00:07:56,880 --> 00:07:59,880
But look, you still made it.

178
00:08:00,360 --> 00:08:01,920
And you look great. Cute, right?

179
00:08:03,040 --> 00:08:06,120
Hello, Pinchas. Hello.

180
00:08:06,400 --> 00:08:07,800
הלו, פנחס. הלו.

181
00:08:07,880 --> 00:08:10,600
Hey, babe. So, Michal, Maldives?

182
00:08:10,680 --> 00:08:12,760
What Maldives? What do you mean Maldives?

183
00:08:12,840 --> 00:08:14,800
Maldives. I thought for Rosh Hashanah I'd surprise you.

184
00:08:14,920 --> 00:08:16,560
And we could just hop over to the Maldives.

185
00:08:16,640 --> 00:08:18,440
What, you decided that just now?

186
00:08:19,360 --> 00:08:20,880
What, is that a surprise? She had no idea?

187
00:08:21,760 --> 00:08:23,360
That's wild, seriously, Shani would kill me

188
00:08:23,480 --> 00:08:25,160
if I made decisions like that on my own.

189
00:08:26,080 --> 00:08:27,120
Maldives?

190
00:08:27,200 --> 00:08:29,160
Honestly, it's a Muslim country, come on, Shai.

191
00:08:29,240 --> 00:08:32,320
Maldives. Yeah, right, Maldives, babe. What do you think?

192
00:08:33,440 --> 00:08:35,960
Cool, how fun.

193
00:08:36,120 --> 00:08:37,080
Karin from my class was there,

194
00:08:37,200 --> 00:08:39,480
she says it's amazing, like, just incredible.

195
00:08:39,640 --> 00:08:41,679
Great, babe. Well, great, babe.

196
00:08:42,000 --> 00:08:43,039
Incredible.

197
00:08:45,840 --> 00:08:49,360
Tell me, why are you making a fuss? What do you care about going to the Hassons for the holiday?

198
00:08:49,440 --> 00:08:51,520
Why are you putting words in my mouth?

199
00:08:51,960 --> 00:08:55,440
I didn't say I care, I said I prefer not to go.

200
00:08:55,520 --> 00:08:57,120
But why? Because I just don't feel like it.

201
00:08:57,280 --> 00:08:59,000
Don't feel like it? You?

202
00:08:59,080 --> 00:09:02,160
Do you know what traffic is like during the holiday? Come on, I'll drive.

203
00:09:02,800 --> 00:09:04,640
Seriously, do me a favor.

204
00:09:04,800 --> 00:09:05,680
You're just being stubborn,

205
00:09:05,760 --> 00:09:08,000
you know it’ll save you all the cooking. Have you thought about that?

206
00:09:08,080 --> 00:09:12,320
I don't mind cooking. Come on, Rebecca, your excuses are running out.

207
00:09:12,400 --> 00:09:15,520
Give me another minute, I'll find you three more besides that.

208
00:09:15,720 --> 00:09:19,080
I want to know what Adam is doing. I'm not leaving him alone for the holiday.

209
00:09:19,160 --> 00:09:20,200
Okay, okay.

210
00:09:20,680 --> 00:09:23,720
Smadar is coming and you're messing with my head about the Hasson family.

211
00:09:24,280 --> 00:09:26,560
I need to take the pastries out of the freezer.

212
00:09:26,640 --> 00:09:28,760
Okay, dear God.

213
00:09:30,240 --> 00:09:31,080
So amazing.

214
00:09:32,720 --> 00:09:33,680
I don't know, just a second.

215
00:09:33,760 --> 00:09:36,480
What's the weather like in the Maldives anyway? I don't know, ask Pinchas.

216
00:09:37,520 --> 00:09:40,400
Shabbat shalom, what's up? Is there food? I'm starving.

217
00:09:40,480 --> 00:09:44,400
Mom, what's going on with the food? It's almost ready.

218
00:09:45,520 --> 00:09:49,280
When Smadar arrives, tell her to come up. Okay, okay.

219
00:09:49,360 --> 00:09:50,960
What Smadar? Why would she come up?

220
00:09:51,920 --> 00:09:53,080
I'll get back to you.

221
00:09:53,200 --> 00:09:56,040
I read an article in the newspaper about her husband, who just became a partner in gas.

222
00:09:56,120 --> 00:09:58,680
She caught a husband, huh? She succeeded this time, huh?

223
00:09:58,800 --> 00:09:59,640
What's up, guys?

224
00:09:59,720 --> 00:10:01,520
Babe, can you come here for a sec? I want to talk to you for a moment.

225
00:10:04,040 --> 00:10:04,880
Shut up, you idiots.

226
00:10:11,440 --> 00:10:13,400
So, Adam, what's new? Everything good.

227
00:10:13,880 --> 00:10:15,840
Yeah, living the dream? We're trying.

228
00:10:16,640 --> 00:10:18,600
Speaking of dreams, where will you be for Rosh Hashanah?

229
00:10:19,360 --> 00:10:21,040
How should I know? What, that's in 30 days, right?

230
00:10:21,120 --> 00:10:22,080
A month away.

231
00:10:22,160 --> 00:10:23,720
Oh, where did the dust go? Did you vacuum?

232
00:10:25,040 --> 00:10:26,160
Why are you asking?

233
00:10:26,240 --> 00:10:27,640
No, because Itamar and Michal are in the Maldives.

234
00:10:27,720 --> 00:10:30,400
And my parents invited your family. Wait a second,

235
00:10:31,440 --> 00:10:33,880
cool, so that means I'm off the hook, I can do the holiday alone,

236
00:10:34,320 --> 00:10:36,920
cool, extreme. Seriously, cool.

237
00:10:37,240 --> 00:10:39,360
What's cool? Mom, come here for a sec.

238
00:10:40,320 --> 00:10:42,000
What happened? No, nothing happened,

239
00:10:42,560 --> 00:10:45,320
Adam decided he's doing the holiday alone. Cool, right?

240
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:48,000
In Nasser's grave, that might be cool,

241
00:10:48,080 --> 00:10:49,000
This isn't happening.

242
00:10:49,120 --> 00:10:51,600
Where did you drag Bazir from now, oh my God.

243
00:10:51,880 --> 00:10:53,400
Pinchas, do me a favor,

244
00:10:53,640 --> 00:10:57,520
