269
00:12:04,680 --> 00:12:05,680
You think so?

270
00:12:05,760 --> 00:12:07,600
Okay, listen for a second, that’s not what I wanted to talk to you about.

271
00:12:07,720 --> 00:12:09,960
Is there a chance we can postpone the Maldives to Yom Kippur?

272
00:12:10,040 --> 00:12:11,440
What’s Yom Kippur?

273
00:12:11,520 --> 00:12:13,320
Because my mom is hosting the holiday at her place this year.

274
00:12:13,440 --> 00:12:15,240
Come? Well, we’ve never been to my mom’s for the holiday.

275
00:12:15,320 --> 00:12:18,080
We’ve never been to Sachne either, so what? Well, that’s not nice.

276
00:12:18,160 --> 00:12:20,840
But, babe, well, fine, if you don’t want to, then it doesn’t matter.

277
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:23,640
No way.

278
00:12:25,880 --> 00:12:27,160
Okay, then I’m calling.

279
00:12:27,240 --> 00:12:28,280
Yeah, yeah, call your mom.

280
00:12:28,360 --> 00:12:31,160
No, suddenly you remember Mom’s sweets.

281
00:12:31,240 --> 00:12:33,280
You can’t have sweets. Well, but I can.

282
00:12:33,360 --> 00:12:35,360
No, it’s not good for you either, it gives you worms.

283
00:12:35,440 --> 00:12:39,680
And Shani, when you call your mom, tell her I’m not eating goat.

284
00:12:40,520 --> 00:12:44,120
Goat? What do you mean goat? We don’t have goats, Riki.

285
00:12:44,200 --> 00:12:46,520
Sit down, you can’t know.

286
00:12:47,240 --> 00:12:49,840
Riki, I know very well. We don’t have goats, what goats?

287
00:12:51,000 --> 00:12:51,960
I’m going to call them.

288
00:12:53,400 --> 00:12:54,320
So what, Adam,

289
00:12:55,440 --> 00:12:56,440
do you remember Meirav?

290
00:12:57,600 --> 00:12:59,920
Shani’s sister? Well, what, she still hasn’t married?

291
00:13:00,720 --> 00:13:02,680
She’d be really happy if you came.

292
00:13:03,240 --> 00:13:04,160
Really.

293
00:13:04,520 --> 00:13:06,960
No way. Well, I don’t understand what your problem is

294
00:13:07,040 --> 00:13:09,120
with us being three on the holiday.

295
00:13:09,800 --> 00:13:12,640
We’ll light candles, sing holiday songs.

296
00:13:12,880 --> 00:13:14,720
I can print song sheets.

297
00:13:14,800 --> 00:13:16,760
Dad will wait for us, animals. Well, yeah.

298
00:13:20,400 --> 00:13:22,400
I’m going to Shani’s parents. Well, yeah, yeah.

299
00:13:22,600 --> 00:13:23,480
No way.

300
00:13:24,560 --> 00:13:25,440
No way.

301
00:13:28,800 --> 00:13:30,120
What's her problem now?

302
00:13:30,320 --> 00:13:33,520
No problem at all, Mom, they'll come! They'll be happy to come.

303
00:13:33,720 --> 00:13:35,120
They'll even bring Adam.

304
00:13:35,200 --> 00:13:36,800
Is it final? Yep, definitely final.

305
00:13:37,080 --> 00:13:38,840
Hey, Mom, I wanted to ask you,

306
00:13:39,800 --> 00:13:41,360
Are you cooking something with goats?

307
00:13:41,920 --> 00:13:43,480
No, why would I cook goats?

308
00:13:43,560 --> 00:13:45,720
I don't know, just asking, never mind.

309
00:13:45,800 --> 00:13:48,840
Sit, sit, wait a sec with Mom, come here.

310
00:13:49,400 --> 00:13:51,440
Okay, Mom... I told you she'd cause trouble.

311
00:13:52,040 --> 00:13:54,360
Why would I cook goats? Who cooks goats?

312
00:13:54,440 --> 00:13:55,840
Bye, Mom, I'll talk to you later.

313
00:13:57,560 --> 00:14:00,560
Come on, babe, you're without kids, we can celebrate at my mom's.

314
00:14:00,640 --> 00:14:02,520
But babe, think about it,

315
00:14:03,080 --> 00:14:05,720
Maldives, just you and me, alone,

316
00:14:06,480 --> 00:14:10,760
no kids, no family, white sand, blue sea, peace and quiet.

317
00:14:10,960 --> 00:14:12,520
All you hear is

318
00:14:14,200 --> 00:14:16,160
What’s that? Oh, it’s the sound of the waves, babe.

319
00:14:16,240 --> 00:14:18,280
Tamari, I didn’t know you were here.

320
00:14:18,920 --> 00:14:19,960
So, are you listening?

321
00:14:20,040 --> 00:14:21,200
Do I have a choice? Nope.

322
00:14:21,480 --> 00:14:23,480
So, if I'm not mistaken,

323
00:14:24,040 --> 00:14:27,160
the kids should be with you for Rosh Hashanah

324
00:14:27,320 --> 00:14:29,200
because they were with Smadar's parents for Passover.

325
00:14:29,280 --> 00:14:30,520
I don’t know, I hadn’t thought about it.

326
00:14:31,080 --> 00:14:34,400
So think, because those are your kids. Yeah, I think you’re right.

327
00:14:34,480 --> 00:14:36,200
Of course I’m right.

328
00:14:36,320 --> 00:14:38,960
So what, are you taking the kids to the Maldives now?

329
00:14:39,040 --> 00:14:40,400
The kids are with you for the holiday?

330
00:14:41,320 --> 00:14:43,320
What do we do? I'll tell you what we do,

331
00:14:43,400 --> 00:14:45,640
