480
00:21:28,760 --> 00:21:31,400
Did you tell her not to bring anything? I don’t understand why she insists.

481
00:21:31,960 --> 00:21:33,720
It's not tasty to anyone anyway.

482
00:21:34,320 --> 00:21:36,360
I told her, she won't bring anything, Mom.

483
00:21:36,440 --> 00:21:38,240
Is it final? Well, it's settled.

484
00:21:38,360 --> 00:21:39,840
I'm on my way home, Mom.

485
00:21:41,680 --> 00:21:43,600
K'no! And `nubenrnorino'no'ben A. `ben.

486
00:21:44,520 --> 00:21:45,520
Hey, Rachel.

487
00:21:45,600 --> 00:21:48,960
Don't get me wrong, I love your mom's cooking.

488
00:21:50,280 --> 00:21:51,920
Good week. Well, good week.

489
00:21:52,920 --> 00:21:55,000
What peace, a little quiet at last.

490
00:21:55,640 --> 00:21:57,400
I swear, no one wants these holidays.

491
00:21:57,480 --> 00:21:58,640
I agree with you—

492
00:21:58,720 --> 00:22:01,000
By the way, for the holiday, I'll be with Moshe's family.

493
00:22:08,160 --> 00:22:11,400
If I'm not mistaken! If I remember correctly,

494
00:22:11,480 --> 00:22:15,000
The kids were at... they need...

495
00:22:22,720 --> 00:22:24,200
Is there a chance I can postpone Yom Kippur?

496
00:22:24,960 --> 00:22:26,920
You postpone Yom Kippur?

497
00:22:27,040 --> 00:22:28,560
As far as I'm concerned, cancel it. Well, it doesn't sit well with me.

498
00:22:30,120 --> 00:22:33,760
What's the problem with the three of us being together for the holiday?

499
00:22:34,400 --> 00:22:37,720
I'll light the candles, we'll sing Hanukkah songs.

500
00:22:37,920 --> 00:22:39,960
I can print song sheets. Well, Dad...

501
00:22:40,800 --> 00:22:45,560
Hanukkah songs on Rosh Hashanah? Well, let's do a pick-up.

502
00:22:45,640 --> 00:22:47,120
Don't be afraid of anyone.

503
00:22:48,680 --> 00:22:50,240
This time she really went too far. Totally.

504
00:22:50,360 --> 00:22:52,120
Dad, what are you...

